#X text 410 301 open for equation details ------------>, f 21;
#X text 59 17 All filters promote phase distortion \, but the Allpass filter only promotes that. A 1st order allpass can be implemented with [rzero_rev~] & [rpole~]. The Pole & Zero effect on the amplitude gets cancelled out \, so only the phase is affected and distorted/shifted! See below the filter equations and how to merge them in [fexpr~]. See also the diagram and transfer function. To the right we convert from hertz to radians per sample and then to the filter coefficient (a). Note that a 1st order allpass shifts the phase from 0 at DC (0 hz) to pi at Nyquist. The frequency input then sets where the 90 degress (pi/2) shift is., f 78;
